history.text: Hello, can you tell me about the movie?
Are you there?
Sorry about that!
no worries!
so can you tell me a little about the movie?
So it's a comedy, kids movie, and it's animated
oh, sounds good!  is it one adults can enjoy, too?
Kids love it a lot, it's got Kristen Bell as one of the main characters
what is it called?
Yeah, I guess adults like it! It's called Frozen
oh I would love to see that!  I've heard it's great
so it has a great cast?
Yeah it's pretty great the first time, I would hate to be a parent having to hear my kids watch it all the time though.
oh yeah well hopefully mine are too young to parrot back parts of it
Yeah it's got Kristen Bell as Anna, Idina Menzel as Elsa, and Jonathan Gross as Kristoff
ok well the cast always helps
It's a Disney movie so they found really good vocalists and actors to do the movie
that's true, Disney usually does a good job with their films
Critics say that it was the animated musical to come out since the Little Mermaid
wow, really?  I sure did notice it getting a lot of acclaim
It came out in 2013, wow I didn't realize it was already that old! Half a decade!
yeah I didn't either.  yikes
how do we know when to stop here or what?
I"m a bit unclear.
12 chat lines for each of us.
ohh, okay.  are there several other movies?
Anyways it got an 89% on rotten tomatos and a CinemaScore of A+
my oldest daughter keeps mentioning wanting to watch it
I feel like rotten tomatos is usually pretty accurate
You should get it for her! I'm sure she would love it. It's a very classic style Disney tale but with all the modern trimmings
I think that I will.  I just haven't decided if my husband and I would like it too b ut I guess we could try.  her little sister will love it too I'm sure althouogh she won't follow the plot
One critic said "Frozen is both a declaration of Disney's renewed cultural relevance and a reaffirmation of Disney coming to terms with its own legacy and identity"
wow, that's deep
well I believe I will put it on our list to watch, or perhaps get it at Redbox.  maybe it's on Netflix if it's that old.
Yeah it's also the 53rd Disney animated film. and it's based off a fairy tale called "The Snow Queen"
oh, I've heard of that fairy tale.  cool, we will lookk that up
Anyways, it was great talking with you! Have a great day!
hard to believe there are so many Disney m ovies
you too!!

uid2response.feedback: It sounds like an interesting movie and one that was very popular with other users.  I think my kids would enjoy it.  I will probably try it.
